                      Key:&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="diffAdd">Additions</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="diffRemove">Deletions</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div id="versionCompareContent" class="WPC-editableContent">
                    <font size="2"><img align="bottom" alt="Garcia" height="153" src="http://image.wetpaint.com/image/1/FwfAP660bVEMdkf-Uty8_Q27006/GW120H153" title="Garcia" width="120" /><br />
                    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />
                    <br />
                    <b>Character Level</b>: 60<br />
                    <b>Location</b>: See the quest (ends in Auch)<br />
                    <b>Job</b>: Fighter, brother to Eduardo<br />
                    <b>Armor</b>: Leather (Generic &amp; Fighter)<br />
                    <b>Weapon Usage</b>: Rapier, Pistol<br />
                    <b>Status</b>:<br /></font>
                    <table align="bottom" cellpadding="3" class="WPC-edit-border-all" width="400">
                      <tbody>
                        <tr>
                          <td align="center" width="16%"><font size="2"><b><font color="#FF0000">Str</font></b><br /></font></td>
                          <td align="center" width="16%"><font size="2"><b><font color="#FF0000">Agi</font></b><br /></font></td>
                          <td align="center" width="16%"><font size="2"><b><font color="#FF0000">Con</font></b><br /></font></td>
                          <td align="center" width="16%"><font size="2"><b><font color="#FF0000">Dex</font></b><br /></font></td>
                          <td align="center" width="16%"><font size="2"><b><font color="#FF0000">Int</font></b><br /></font></td>
                          <td align="center" width="16%"><font size="2"><b><font color="#FF0000">Cha</font></b><br /></font></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                          <td align="center" width="16%"><font size="2">6<br /></font></td>
                          <td align="center" width="16%"><font size="2">5<br /></font></td>
                          <td align="center" width="16%"><font size="2">6<br /></font></td>
                          <td align="center" width="16%"><font size="2">7<br /></font></td>
                          <td align="center" width="16%"><font size="2">3<br /></font></td>
                          <td align="center" width="16%"><font size="2">3<br /></font></td>
                        </tr>
                      </tbody>
                    </table><font size="2"><br />
                    <b>Stances</b>:<br /></font>
                    <blockquote>
                      <ul>
                        <li><font size="2">Epee Garde</font></li>
                        <li><font size="2">Sabre Garde</font></li>
                        <li><font size="2">Avant Garde</font></li>
                        <li><font size="2">Aiming Shot</font><br /></li>
                        <li><font size="2">Freestyle Shot<br /></font></li>
                        <li><font size="2">Double-Gun Shot</font><br /></li>
                        <li><font size="2">Sight Shot</font></li>
                        <li><font size="2">Outrage Shot</font></li>
                      </ul>
                    </blockquote><font size="2"><b>Comments: He is the brother of Eduardo.<br />
                    <br /></b></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <b>Garcia Video</b><br />
                      <br />
                      <font color="#0000FF" face="Helvetica" size="5"><br /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><b><br /></b><br />
                    <b><br /></b><b>How to get:<br /></b></font> <font size="2">Please ensure that you have finished the following quests otherwise you cannot activate his quest:<br />
                    <br />
                    - The Pioneering quest (finishing the Bahamas Swamp section)<br />
                    - The Katovic Snowfield quest series, at least until the soup portion.<br />
                    <br /></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <font size="2"><img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" height="338" src="http://i236.photobucket.com/albums/ff132/conversehacz/ele-2.png" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" width="450" /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><br />
                    <i>Start with Elenore&rsquo;s request at Auch.</i><br />
                    <br /></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <font size="2"><img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" height="338" src="http://i236.photobucket.com/albums/ff132/conversehacz/pillar.png" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" width="450" /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><br />
                    <i>Joaquin Expedition</i><br />
                    <br />
                    Continuing on, Elenore the Auch Pioneering Officer will ask you to catch Garcia, but she will send you to do an instanced mission called the Joaquin Expedition.<br />
                    <br /></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <font size="2"><img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" height="338" src="http://i236.photobucket.com/albums/ff132/conversehacz/simon.png" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" width="450" /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><br />
                    <i>Simon&rsquo;s proposal - accept or decline</i><br />
                    <br />
                    Once you&rsquo;re done, head on and talk to Simon Ayende first. He will offer you two options, which would alter the storyline a little but no matter which option you chose you will still get Garcia&rsquo;s card for both routes.<br />
                    <br /></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <font size="2"><img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" height="338" src="http://i236.photobucket.com/albums/ff132/conversehacz/wall.png" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" width="450" /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><br />
                    <i>Location - Ferrucio Wall (F2)</i><br />
                    This leg of the quest entails pretty much just trekking to the wall. Step around the given coordinates and hope the quest triggers.<br />
                    <br /></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <font size="2"><img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" height="338" src="http://i236.photobucket.com/albums/ff132/conversehacz/meet.png" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" width="450" /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><br />
                    <i>Meeting Selva Notre</i><br />
                    <br />
                    After receiving either of the two missions, head to Ferrucio Wall, and there you will meet Selva. After some dialogue, go to the Frozen Plain and talk to Invernio to continue investigation of Feruccio&rsquo;s legacy. You will bump into Selva and Garcia again.<br />
                    <br /></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <font size="2"><img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" height="338" src="http://i236.photobucket.com/albums/ff132/conversehacz/frozen.png" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" width="450" /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><br />
                    <i>Invernio&rsquo;s location</i><br />
                    <br />
                    Touching Ryrin&rsquo;s Heart would allow you to know what exactly is Ferrucio&rsquo;s legacy, but before that, you need 50 philosopher&#39;s stones, 50 ice crystals and 10 cursed determinations. The philosopher&#39;s stones and ice crystals drop all over the snowfields. The cursed determinations can be obtained by using the ghost nukes towards the Ryrin&#39;s Hearts. You will gain the 10 ghost nukes from Invierno at the start of this leg of the quest. To use them, simply drag the item icon towards a Ryrin&#39;s Heart. A noonbara ghost of sorts will spawn. You will need to kill 10 of these and hence, use everyone of your ghost nukes.<br />
                    <br /></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <font size="2"><img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" height="338" src="http://i236.photobucket.com/albums/ff132/conversehacz/collect.png" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" width="450" /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><br />
                    <br />
                    <br /></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <font size="2"><img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" height="338" src="http://i236.photobucket.com/albums/ff132/conversehacz/mon.png" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" width="450" /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><br />
                    <i>6 v 1, fair battle? xD</i><br />
                    <br />
                    After solving the mystery of Reym&rsquo;s heart, Montoro will appear and steal the Ice Queen&rsquo;s seal. Selva, Garcia and Invernio will join your family in battle so you can attack from the corners. Here&rsquo;s Montoro&rsquo;s stats just in case:<br />
                    <br /></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <font size="2"><img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" height="271" src="http://i236.photobucket.com/albums/ff132/conversehacz/montoro.png" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" width="336" /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><br />
                    <i>Montoro&rsquo;s stats</i><br />
                    <br />
                    At this point, you will receive this awesome item that adds 3AR and DR called Necklace of Sage. This item will be in your premium equipment window. It has a timer for 3 days which will activate once you equip it. Be sure not to waste it.<br />
                    <br /></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <font size="2"><img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" height="286" src="http://i236.photobucket.com/albums/ff132/conversehacz/sage.png" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" width="444" /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><br />
                    <i>The pendent will only remain in your inventory for three days and only one character may equip it</i><br />
                    <br />
                    The next mission is to enter Ice Wizard Tower itself and defeat Novia. (Need to finish all katovic quests at this point to enter.)<br />
                    <br /></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <font size="2"><img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" height="338" src="http://i236.photobucket.com/albums/ff132/conversehacz/missionbegins.png" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" width="450" /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><br />
                    Once you entered the Ice Wizard Tower, move forward a few steps and a window will trigger asking you if you want to advance to the mission. Selecting yes will warp you to the instanced mission.<br />
                    <br /></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <font size="2"><img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" height="338" src="http://i236.photobucket.com/albums/ff132/conversehacz/fight.png" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" width="450" /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><br />
                    Once you&rsquo;re warped to the mission the battle will start against Novia. This will be no easy battle as you will not only face off Novia, but with her &ldquo;summons&rdquo; and Montoro. Selva and Garcia will aid you in the battle.<br />
                    <br /></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <font size="2"><img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" height="358" src="http://i236.photobucket.com/albums/ff132/conversehacz/spot.png" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" width="455" /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><br />
                    <b>Note</b>: It is extra important you stand at the following spot as indicated if you even want an easy battle. It will give your family a buff of <b>AR/DR + 5</b> (It used to be 10 but the buff got nerfed as of ver 2.4) .You maybe fighting a quest version of Novia but nevertheless she&rsquo;s still a tough cookie.<br />
                    <br /></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <font size="2"><img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" height="396" src="http://i236.photobucket.com/albums/ff132/conversehacz/stats-4.png" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" width="455" /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><br />
                    <i>lvl 130 = Novia, lvl 110 = Montoro, lvl 120 = Novia&rsquo;s summons</i><br />
                    <br />
                    You need to take down Montoro and her summons, and bring down Novia&rsquo;s HP to 50% before the quest is complete.<br />
                    <br />
                    *Vital battle tip - Bring Elementalists or Vincent; excluding Montoro, the others are very weak to lightning but remember to cover them while they spam away their skills.<br />
                    <br />
                    Let me stress that the fight is really tough, even with 92e armor, Triumph Fillers and AM Boosts. Without the room buff, you&#39;ll likely die within a few seconds. Obtaining the room buff is critical to success. Hence, once the fight starts, immediately move towards the designated location above in order to get the buff. The fight is quite annoying, will likely take multiple tries. To make matters worse, the mission starts with dialogue that can&#39;t be skipped.<br />
                    <br />
                    A good way to win the fight is to use invisible potions once the dialogue finishes. Being invisible causes your characters to lose aggro from the all the monsters/enemies except Montoro. The monsters won&#39;t be able to target you and you can&#39;t use skills. However, you can still attack normally and use items. Therefore, the tactic is to simply keep on drinking potions as you take out the mobs one by one, starting with montoro, then the 3 lizard things and finally, Novia. It is recommended that you keep on drinking potions, keeping the invisibility buff up.<br />
                    <br />
                    Attacking the mobs can be done in 2 ways. The first is via simply quaffing potions and attacking, the second is that, once you lose aggro, head to a far end of the map and wait for Selva and Garcia to die. Once they fall, the monsters will wonder around and if you position yourself right, you can take them out one by one without the need for further invisible potions. Frankly, the method of spamming potions is easier.<br />
                    <br />
                    Once you defeat all the summons and Montoro, you can now focus on Novia. I personally ran out of potions during this phase of the battle but was able to keep my team up by spamming Health Fillers instead. It is still recommended to use invisibility potions as Novia can cause freeze towards your characters. Once your characters go down, they&#39;re likely out and you&#39;ll be one step from failing the mission and wasting potions. Although you can use the resuscitation skill, soul crystals will not work. Due to this, even though you can stay alive with Health Fillers, the invisibility pot is still a good way of insuring success, and may save a dying character.<br />
                    <br />
                    A single invisible potion grants a level 1 invisible stalker that lasts roughly for 15 seconds. You will likely need at <b>least</b> 130 invisible potions for the fight, not counting potions used during unsuccessful attempts. Alternatively, you can also bring a wizard or M&#39;Boma to simply cast the spell, though you&#39;ll likely need a potion or two to draw aggro away from them during the start of the fight. As long as you have 3 characters up by the time you&#39;re up against Novia, you shouldn&#39;t have too much trouble bringing her down. However, if you feel the need for a boost, equip the Sage Necklace for the 3 AR DR boost.<br />
                    <br />
                    It is recommended that before you equip the necklace, get a feel of the fight first. Also, stock up on invisible pots. You don&#39;t need the necklace to win but it&#39;ll help. I brought a vet Musketeer &amp; Elementalist and an expert Fighter. I didn&#39;t take note of the AR of my Fighter and Elementalist, but my Musk had an AR of 58. Even with the room buff, Novia was still able to block most attacks. With the necklace on, I was able to finish with a little over 10 minutes left. Hence, even without the necklace, spamming potions should be enough for you to win. The necklace just makes it somewhat easier and is definitely not needed to win.<br />
                    <br />
                    The fight is quite expensive so even if things are going well, you might not want to take chances. Keep your health up and keep on being invisible. Invisibility is invincibility.<br />
                    <br />
                    After the battle, Garcia will be injured. Talk to Invernio again, and he will tell you that you need 1 soup and 10 gold bars to create a remedy to save Garcia. 1 soup requires 50 Wolf&rsquo;s meat, 20 Golden apples, 50 cabbages and 50 beets.<br />
                    <br />
                    <b>Note:</b> If you have not done the soup quest in the Katovic Snowfield quest section, you will not be able to proceed to this part.<br />
                    <br />
                    After saving Garcia, depending on what you chose when Simon offered you two choices, Garcia will either join you immediately or he will enter into a battle against you. But either way, you will get Garcia&rsquo;s card.<br />
                    <br />
                    <b>Scenario 1</b><br />
                    <br /></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <font size="2"><img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" height="338" src="http://i236.photobucket.com/albums/ff132/conversehacz/decision.png" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" width="450" /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><br />
                    If you chose Simon&rsquo;s second option, which is to report to him after you have found/caught Garcia, you can get Garcia&rsquo;s card as your reward by talking to him back at Auch.<br />
                    <br />
                    <b>Scenario 2</b><br />
                    <br />
                    If you chose Simon&rsquo;s first option, which is to hand him over to the Office of Pioneering Support, you will be engaged into a battle with him.<br />
                    <br /></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <font size="2"><img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" height="168" src="http://i236.photobucket.com/albums/ff132/conversehacz/garcia.png" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" width="319" /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><br />
                    <i>Garcia&rsquo;s stats</i><br />
                    <br />
                    After you win/lose, Garcia will run off and you will need to find him. If you want to know his location, speak with Tiburon (ugh) and he will only tell you Garcia&rsquo;s location if you pay him 1,000,000 Vis.<br />
                    <br /></font>
                    <div align="center">
                      <font size="2"><img alt="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" height="458" src="http://i236.photobucket.com/albums/ff132/conversehacz/tib.png" title="Bahamar - Wiki of the new world" width="455" /></font>
                    </div><font size="2"><br />
                    <i>To those who have done Lorch&rsquo;s quest before, you should know better than to choose the 200,000 Vis offer.</i><br />
                    <br />
                    After you found his location, return to converse with Simon Ayende to receive Garcia&rsquo;s card AND a lvl 100 enchantment chip.<br />
                    <br />
                    <br />
                    <b><br /></b></font>
